Package: perturb
Type: Package
Title: Tools for Evaluating Collinearity
Version: 3.0
Author: John Hendrickx <John.Hendrickx@Danone.com>
Maintainer: John Hendrickx <John.Hendrickx@Danone.com>
Description: Use the perturb() function to evaluates collinearity by adding 
    random noise to selected variables (Hendrickx & Pelzer 2004). Version 3.0
    of perturb() can be used with mixed models by nlme and lme4 (Hendrickx 2018).
    The colldiag function() calculates condition numbers and variance 
    decomposition proportions to test for collinearity and uncover its sources 
    (Belsley 1980).
License: GPL (>= 2)
Imports: gdata
Suggests: 
    car,
    rms,
    lme4,
    nlme,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    lmerTest,
    tidyr,
    ggplot2,
    huxtable
LazyData: true
VignetteBuilder: knitr
